1. Download Docker desktop tool
2. Create a docker-compose.yaml file in your preferred directory. Copy the command in the "Version 3" from this website - https://github.com/SeleniumHQ/docker-selenium
3. Open "Terminal"
4. Execute this command to start the grid : docker-compose -f ./docker/docker-compose.yaml up -d
5. Execute this command to start the grid : docker-compose -f ./docker/docker-compose.yaml down -d